"track\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"a colour\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 377}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic website\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a 'long process' forParis 2024organisers to get it set up.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 'long process' forParis 2024organisers\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But why have they decided to paint the track purple?\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 565, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the track purple\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read on to find out\\u2026 Alain Blondel, the sports manager in charge of athletics for Paris 2024, has explained two key reasons why such an unusual decision was made.\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"score\": 0.9999990810651654, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alain Blondel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\"}, {\"begin\": 649, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.8192597979605117e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sports manager\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 620}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 643}, {\"ngram\": \"two key reasons\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 689}, {\"ngram\": \"such an unusual decision\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first is that Paris 2024 organisers firmly wanted something 'outside the box' - likely to get people talking and build interest - witha huge number of tickets still unsold.\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.8192597979605117e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"the box\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 811}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"interest - witha huge number\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 882}, {\"ngram\": \"tickets\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u009c\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u0083\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00b9:@Paris2024pic.twitter.com/rUhlI4luKS 'The big part of the job was to come up with a track that was different from what we had seen,' Blondel said.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The big part\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"a track\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"Blondel\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'[In order] to maintain the creative approach that the Organising Committee has had since it was set up, to go a little bit outside the box.'\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"the creative approach\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"the Organising Committee\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"the box\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1210}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The second reason is because the colour is said to 'highlight' athletes who will be competing on the track.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The second reason\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1231}, {\"ngram\": \"the colour\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1253}, {\"ngram\": \"'highlight' athletes\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blondel also explained the turns at the end of the bend are grey in tribute to the ash-coloured tracks at the Paris Games back in 1924.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Blondel\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"the turns\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1355}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1366}, {\"ngram\": \"the bend\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1378}, {\"ngram\": \"tribute\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"the ash-coloured tracks\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1425}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The look of the Games includes three colours for all the competition venues: blue, green and purple,' he added.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The look\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"three colours\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics gets underway onWednesday, July 24, 2024with the opening ceremony taking place on Friday, July 26, 2024.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"2024with\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1681}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing ceremony is on Sunday, August 11, 2024.\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The closing ceremony\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1718}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not only the purple running track that's got people talking, there are also a number of bizarre rules at the Games, such as: Wrestlers must carry a handkerchief- Olympic wrestlers must carry a hanky, known as a \\\"bloodrag,\\\" somewhere in their uniform.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 2007, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the purple running track\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1840}, {\"ngram\": \"bizarre rules\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"Wrestlers\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"a handkerchief- Olympic wrestlers\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"bloodrag\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"their uniform\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's used to clean up any bleeding during the competition.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any bleeding\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxers must be clean shaven- Competitors in the boxing competition must be clean-shaven or have very limited facial hair.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boxers\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"clean shaven- Competitors\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"the boxing competition\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2134}, {\"ngram\": \"very limited facial hair\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2188}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxers must be clean shaven to ensure cuts and injuries are easily visible for prompt medical attention and to reduce the risk of abrasions.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boxers\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2196}, {\"ngram\": \"cuts\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"injuries\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2245}, {\"ngram\": \"prompt medical attention\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2293}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"abrasions\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A pencil mustache, however, is allowed.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A pencil mustache\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clean hair only for Karate competitors- Make sure to lather up that shampoo, because karate referees have the authority to disqualify an athlete if they judge their hair to be insufficiently clean.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.029153238091598e-17, \"text\": \"Karate\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Clean hair\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"that shampoo\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2447}, {\"ngram\": \"karate referees\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2472}, {\"ngram\": \"the authority\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2516}, {\"ngram\": \"their hair\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clean hair also reduces the risk of transmitting infections and diseases during close-contact combat.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Clean hair\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2580}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2602}, {\"ngram\": \"transmitting infections\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2629}, {\"ngram\": \"diseases\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2642}, {\"ngram\": \"close-contact combat\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2670}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No groin grabbing in Water Polo- Water polo is a physically demanding sport, but excessive force, including groin grabbing, is strictly prohibited.\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Water Polo-\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2705}, {\"ngram\": \"a physically demanding sport\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"excessive force\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cyclists' socks can only go to mid-calf- In Olympic cycling, there is an unusual uniform rule: socks cannot extend beyond mid-calf length and are subject to measurement, this is in place to maintain fair competition and aerodynamic consistency.\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 3066, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cyclists' socks\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"mid\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2856}, {\"ngram\": \"calf-\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 2862}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic cycling\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2881}, {\"ngram\": \"an unusual uniform rule\", \"from\": 2892, \"to\": 2915}, {\"ngram\": \"socks\", \"from\": 2917, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"mid-calf length\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 2959}, {\"ngram\": \"measurement\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 2990}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3008}, {\"ngram\": \"fair competition\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3037}, {\"ngram\": \"aerodynamic consistency\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Longer socks could provide an aerodynamic advantage by reducing drag, and regulating sock length ensures all cyclists compete under the same conditions.\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3219, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Longer socks\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3079}, {\"ngram\": \"an aerodynamic advantage\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3118}, {\"ngram\": \"drag\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3135}, {\"ngram\": \"sock length\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ng